%% Data Flow Diagram - batch-gateway
%% Generated by: Claude Opus 4.6
%% Source: architecture/rhoai-3.4-ea.1/batch-gateway.md

sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant API as API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP/HTTPS
    participant Redis as Redis<br/>6379/TCP
    participant FS as File Storage<br/>(S3/Filesystem)
    participant Proc as Batch Processor<br/>9090/TCP
    participant IGW as Inference Gateway<br/>(llm-d/GAIE)

    Note over Client,IGW: Flow 1: File Upload
    Client->>API: POST /v1/files (multipart/form-data)<br/>Header: X-MaaS-User
    API->>FS: Store JSONL file<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    API->>Redis: Store file metadata<br/>6379/TCP Password
    API-->>Client: File object (JSON)

    Note over Client,IGW: Flow 2: Batch Job Submission
    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches<br/>Header: X-MaaS-User
    API->>Redis: Store batch job (DB)<br/>6379/TCP Password
    API->>Redis: Enqueue to priority queue<br/>6379/TCP Password
    API-->>Client: Batch object (JSON, status: validating)

    Note over Client,IGW: Flow 3: Batch Job Processing
    Proc->>Redis: Dequeue from priority queue<br/>6379/TCP Password (poll 5s)
    Redis-->>Proc: Batch job data
    Proc->>Redis: Set status: in_progress<br/>6379/TCP Password
    Proc->>FS: Read input JSONL file<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    FS-->>Proc: JSONL lines

    loop For each JSONL line (max 10 concurrent)
        Proc->>IGW: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>HTTP/HTTPS mTLS<br/>Bearer Token
        IGW-->>Proc: Inference result
    end

    Proc->>FS: Write output JSONL file<br/>HTTPS/443 AWS IAM
    Proc->>Redis: Update job + set status: completed<br/>6379/TCP Password

    Note over Client,IGW: Flow 4: Batch Job Cancellation
    Client->>API: POST /v1/batches/{id}/cancel<br/>Header: X-MaaS-User
    API->>Redis: Delete from priority queue<br/>6379/TCP Password
    alt Job is queued
        API->>Redis: Update status: cancelled<br/>6379/TCP Password
    else Job is in-progress
        API->>Redis: Publish cancel event<br/>6379/TCP Password
    end
    API-->>Client: Updated batch object (JSON)
